{"TopicId":206477,"ForumId":24,"TopicTitle":"Hi! I need help to orbit","CreatedByName":"Neptunium_69","CreatedById":218699,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-18T07:09:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Neptunium_69","CreatedById":218699,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-18T07:09:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just started playing the game and I\u2019m having trouble flying to orbit, any tips and instructions?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-18T07:14:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt just so happens that I made a guide for this sort of thing. I haven\u0027t updated it for a long time but it should still be helpful.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002227914\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6498254069\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/115750-how-to-reach-orbit-and-a-sandbox-rocket-to-do-it-with/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:198px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, welcome to the forum. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-18T09:02:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, for beginners, you should lower the throttle a bit and turn 45\u00B0 until apoapsis is over 70km. I recommend 80km the best. Then either make a maneuver node at apoapsis to get you in a circular orbit. Then from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E options, turn to the blue maneuver node marker, next to stability assist. Burn at half the burn time before the node. For example: You should burn for 40 seconds, so you should start your burn at T-20 seconds before you reach the node. Or you can burn prograde a little before apoapsis.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neptunium_69","CreatedById":218699,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-19T03:26:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks! I already got my rocket ready and did a abort test, orbital flight is so close!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-19T04:07:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWorking up to it by steps is a smart approach. Good luck.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Neptunium_69","CreatedById":218699,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-21T03:02:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI DID IT\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-21T04:37:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGreat feeling, isn\u0027t it? Now you can just sit there and watch the terrain roll by.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Maria Sirona","CreatedById":210882,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-21T08:45:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224080145\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022206477\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221642734134\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218699\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Smart Boy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Smart Boy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI DID IT\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh that is so awesome! Congratulations! Also welcome to the forums!\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-01-21T09:24:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCongrats, mate! Thats the first step to even more space exploration! (rendezvous, docking, mun, minmus, interplanetary, asteroids, etc...!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd welcome to the forums!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}